                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00113 E.W./10–544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-05">October 5,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received October 5—11:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6637. American Interests—Bulgaria—Private Property. Swiss Legation, Sofia,
                    telegraphs Bulgarian decree September 15 abrogates all valid laws concerning
                    enemy property, terminates sequestrations and orders restitution property to
                    owners.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
